10/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski reiterated Thursday (9 October) that Macedonia expects to receive a clear signal next year that it will be invited to join NATO in 2006. 
In an interview with the Japanese daily <I>Keizai Shimbun</I>, he said that Skopje is reforming its military to meet NATO membership criteria on time. 
He added that Macedonia's accession would strengthen security in Southeast Europe. 
Asked about recurring incidents in the former crisis regions, Trajkovski said they were provoked by individuals or small groups who lack support among the local population. 
(MIA - 09/10/03)
